Ok, before I go any further, let me ask the same question I have asked
everyone else recently on the list.  "Which guy are you again?"  lol  I
met so many damn people this weekend that I can't keep up.  No offense
of course.  I did get the seals changed for two injectors, and replaced
all the fuel lines on that side, except the one going through the
firewall. (It was 12am.)  It idles much better now.  Cant wait to do the
other side.  So, only having three sets of seals, I called Joe at Busted
Bus and ordered another set to complete the other side.  I also ordered
7mm fuel line and enough clamps to replace all of the exsisting ones.
Question though, on the short fuel line going to the injector, there is
not a clamp around the fuel line at the injector side.  There was a
flange looking thing that the fuel line had been pressed into.  May I
had that this was a b*#tch to get the old fuel line out of!!  What
should be done here when replacing that short piece? Oh, also got a new
rubber engine seal to replace around the tin.

